1 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES - FLOOR VERSION
2 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
3 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
4 HOUSE BILL 3322 By: Osburn of the House
5 and
6 Howard of the Senate
7
8
9 AS INTRODUCED
10 An Act relating to statutes and reports; amending 75
O.S. 2021, Section 11a, which relates to statutory
11 interpretation; providing for construction of certain
amendatory enactments; stating legislative intent;
12 creating presumption; and providing an effective
date.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 75 O.S. 2021, Section 11a, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 11a. In the construction of the statutes of this state,
19 the following rules shall be observed:
20 1. For any act enacted on or after July 1, 1989, unless there
21 is a provision in the act that the act or any portion thereof or the
22 application of the act shall not be severable, the provisions of
23 every act or application of the act shall be severable. If any
24 provision or application of the act is found to be unconstitutional
HB3322 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 and void, the remaining provisions or applications of the act shall
2 remain valid, unless the court finds:
3 a. the valid provisions or application of the act are so
4 essentially and inseparably connected with, and so
5 dependent upon, the void provisions that the court
6 cannot presume the Legislature would have enacted the
7 remaining valid provisions without the void one; or
8 b. the remaining valid provisions or applications of the
9 act, standing alone, are incomplete and are incapable
10 of being executed in accordance with the legislative
11 intent.
12 2. For acts enacted prior to July 1, 1989, whether or not such
13 acts were enacted with an express provision for severability, it is
14 the intent of the Oklahoma Legislature that the act or any portion
15 of the act or application of the act shall be severable unless:
16 a. the construction of the provisions or application of
17 the act would be inconsistent with the manifest intent
18 of the Legislature;
19 b. the court finds the valid provisions of the act are so
20 essentially and inseparably connected with and so
21 dependent upon the void provisions that the court
22 cannot presume the Legislature would have enacted the
23 remaining valid provisions without the void one; or
24
HB3322 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 c. the court finds the remaining valid provisions
2 standing alone, are incomplete and are incapable of
3 being executed in accordance with the legislative
4 intent.
5 3. When acts amend the same statute or statutes, whether in the
6 same or different sessions of the Legislature, creating multiple
7 versions of the same statute or statutes it is the intent of the
8 Oklahoma Legislature that:
9 a. when possible, the acts are to be construed together
10 to determine the intent of the Legislature,
11 reconciling provisions, rendering them consistent and
12 giving intelligent effect to each act;
13 b. repeal by implication is disfavored;
14 c. language in amendatory measures that is neither
15 underlined nor stricken through is not intended to
16 change the statute but is only reproduced to provide
17 context and placement to the amendatory language;
18 d. acts which do not purport by citation to amend the
19 other version or versions of the same statute are
20 presumed to be reconcilable and not to conflict or
21 contravene one another; and
22 e. if the same section of law has been amended in two or
23 more measures and as a result of the enactment of
24 those measures the official statutes of the State of
HB3322 HFLR Page 3
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 Oklahoma contain two or more versions of the same
2 section of law, if it is possible to determine the
3 exact date and time as of which each measure was
4 enacted as law, there shall be a presumption that the
5 measure enacted latest in time contains the
6 Legislature's intent if there is a conflict between or
7 among the versions which cannot be avoided by
8 construing both or all versions of the statute
9 together. As used in this subparagraph "enacted as
10 law" shall mean the date, hour and minute the measure
11 was signed by the Governor.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
13
